G-CHAT-B3-DISPOSER (v9d)  Δ-CONTINUATION signal (real-E vs zeroed-E, first-gen token)
=======================================================================================
Same speculative inject→score→O(1)-rewind plumbing as the Yes/No Disposer, signal swapped.
DIFFERENTIAL against the SAME query: per candidate inject REAL E then ZEROED E (zero=true ⇒
same npos = same RoPE/position shift, null content), decode_step(last) under each, measure
divergence of the two first-gen distributions. Logs KL(real‖zero), L1, max-mass-gain (mg).
Rank on KL. Telemetry-first (TAU=+inf, never fires). Registry: ep_wiki/Boulter(84),
ep_homarus/lobster(180), ep_headlam/Headlam(179); M_target=42; greedy.

PRE-REGISTERED GATE: matched episode = per-query argmax AND min(matched) > max(foreign).

KL MATRIX (mg in parens where notable):
  q (→matched)              wiki        homarus    headlam     argmax(KL)
  q1 Boulter (→wiki)        0.200       1.653      2.215       headlam   MISS
  q2 lobster (→homarus)     0.983       1.318      1.961       headlam   MISS
  q3 Headlam (→headlam)     0.717       0.919      1.107       headlam   HIT
  q4 sourdough-boulter (F)  0.469       0.571      0.499       homarus
  q5 dp4a GEMV (F)          0.918(.241) 0.455      0.534       wiki
  q6 remember (F)           0.593       0.064      0.190       wiki
  q7 stopwords (F)          0.058       0.194      0.180       homarus
  q8 France (F)             0.414       0.456      0.399       homarus
  q9 sourdough (F)          0.674       0.310      0.428       wiki

VERDICT: GATE FAILED, but STRICTLY BETTER than Yes/No and INFORMATIVE.
  * Diagonal dominance 1/3 (vs Yes/No 0/3): q3 matched=argmax. Real query-structure now
    visible (q5 dp4a → wiki mg-spike 0.241; not pure baseline). The per-episode YES-BIAS
    is GONE (the differential cancelled it).
  * Two confounds replaced it, both diagnosed on the metal:
    1. CONTENT-MAGNITUDE bias — KL scales with how much content E injects, so headlam/homarus
       (npos≈180) out-shift wiki (npos 84) regardless of relevance. The zeroed control removed
       the POSITION shift but NOT the amount-of-content shift. Needs per-episode normalization.
    2. FIRST-TOKEN IS TOO EARLY (the real killer). On "Who is Boulter?" the MATCHED Boulter
       episode gives the SMALLEST shift (0.200). A biographical answer opens with a generic
       token ("Robert"/"He"/"A") identical whether the memory is real or zeroed; the
       memory-specific facts ("The Bill","Herons") surface POSITIONS 3-8 downstream. Measuring
       only position 1 is blind to the relevance signal.

DIAGNOSIS → NEXT (same plumbing): MULTI-TOKEN Δ-continuation. Greedily decode the first ~8
tokens under REAL E; score that SAME token sequence's NLL under ZEROED E; signal = the per-token
log-prob GAIN that the real content gives the on-topic continuation, summed over positions 3-8
(where facts surface), normalized per-episode (divide by the episode's self-shift to kill the
content-magnitude bias). This is the teacher-forced ΔLL on the model's OWN answer — relevant
memory RAISES the prob of the continuation it produced; irrelevant memory does not.
Yes/No 0/3 (pure bias) → first-token Δcont 1/3 (real structure, wrong depth) → multi-token Δcont
(facts surface) is the falsifiable ladder. M_target=42 budget remains the safety floor.

NOTE: the test episodes are WIKI passages about real entities; without memory the 12B confabulates
them (α=0.2 "Who is Boulter?" → "British artist/D&D", a hallucination), so memory IS additive —
the signal failure is depth/normalization, NOT a known-answer redundancy.

CODE: tools/sp_daemon/src/routes.rs (SP_B3_DISPOSER, Δcont; telemetry-default TAU=+inf = null floor).
